      <body>
         <div>
            <entry xml:id="Lcaf3b0592b1f45a294a99f80d81b33c7" n="12780">
               <form><foreign xml:lang="gez">ብስጥ</foreign></form>
               <sense xml:id="Tmain" xml:lang="en" source="#traces">
                  <cit type="transcription" xml:lang="gez">
                     <quote>bǝsṭ</quote>
                  </cit>
                  <gramGrp><pos expand="Substantivum">subst.</pos></gramGrp> large cotton fabric
                        (<bibl><ptr target="bm:ContiRossini1910LiberV"/><citedRange unit="page"> 60
                        n. 3</citedRange></bibl>, see also his comment below); considered also as an
                  ortographic variant (<bibl><ptr target="bm:Abbadie1881Dict"/><citedRange unit="page"> 353</citedRange></bibl>) or the singular form of <lbl expand="videas">vid.</lbl>
                  <foreign xml:lang="gez">ብሳጥ፡</foreign> (<bibl><ptr target="bm:Guidi1901Vocabolario"/><citedRange unit="page">
                     332b</citedRange></bibl>) with the meaning ‘carpet’, <foreign xml:lang="gez">፩ዝንጕርጕር፡ ብስጥ፡</foreign> ‘<cit type="translation" xml:lang="fr">
                     <quote>des étoffes appelées besṭ, de plusieurs couleurs</quote>
                  </cit>’ <bibl><ptr target="bm:ContiRossini1909LiberT"/><citedRange unit="page"> 50
                        l. 6 (ed.)</citedRange></bibl>, <bibl><ptr target="bm:ContiRossini1910LiberV"/><citedRange unit="page"> 60 l. 6
                        (tr.)</citedRange></bibl>; <foreign xml:lang="gez">፩ግብረ፡ መርፌ፡ ብስጥ፡</foreign>
                     ‘<cit type="translation" xml:lang="fr">
                     <quote>un besṭ brodé</quote>
                  </cit>’ <bibl><ptr target="bm:ContiRossini1909LiberT"/><citedRange unit="page"> 65
                        l. 18–19 (ed.)</citedRange></bibl>, <bibl><ptr target="bm:ContiRossini1910LiberV"/><citedRange unit="page"> 79 l. 4–5
                        (tr.)</citedRange></bibl> (‘Besṭ, grosses étoffes de coton, de fabrication
                  indigène; on les donnait au roi en payment des impôts; les riches s’en servent
                  pour se coucher la nuit. Cf. <bibl><ptr target="bm:Alvarez1889PresteJoao"/><citedRange unit="page"> 153</citedRange></bibl>; <bibl><ptr target="bm:Paez1905HistAeth"/><citedRange unit="page">
                     284</citedRange></bibl>.’ <bibl><ptr target="bm:ContiRossini1910LiberV"/><citedRange unit="page"> 60 n. 3</citedRange></bibl>) <nd/>
               </sense>
